<1ST_LINE>r i PM-BRF--Spain-Terror     05-26 0115</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Spain-Terror,0118</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Restaurant Owner Killed In Northern Spain</HEAD>
<DATELINE>EIBAR, Spain (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A restaurant owner was shot and killed in
this Basque town near San Sebastian in what provincial government
officials said appeared to be the work of the Basque separatist
group ETA.
   According to witnesses, one or two men shot and killed Sebastian
Azpiri, 38, as he walked to his restaurant on Wednesday night.
   ETA has claimed responsibility for the deaths of three policemen
and a retired general so far this year.
   Since taking up arms in 1968, the separatist group has claimed
more than 600 killings in its campaign to seek independence from
Spain for the three-province Basque region in northern Spain.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
