<1ST_LINE>r i PM-BRF--Israel-Accident     05-26 0167</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Israel-Accident,0171</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Three Israeli Workers Killed In Ship Accident</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JERUSALEM (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Three Israeli longshoremen were killed and one
was badly injured by poisonous gas in the hull of a Belgian coal
ship they were cleaning in Hadera port, Israel Television said.
   The Energy Ministry named a commission of inquiry to investigate
the accident on Wednesday aboard the vessel Orinocco Antwerpen, it
said.
   The vessel had been docked at Hadera, 30 miles north of Tel
Aviv, since Sunday to unload its cargo of Australian coal.
   The dock workers were descending into one of the nine storage
tanks to prepare it for reloading.
   ``The door was open and one went down. We didn't hear him from
the top so a second went down. After him a third, a fourth. Finally
the fifth realized something was wrong and alerted the ship's
crew,'' Uri Binder, manager of the cleaning company, told Israel
Television.
   It was not immediately clear what type of gas was involved or
where it came from.
</TEXT>
