<1ST_LINE>u a AM-LeopardAttack     05-26 0248</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Leopard Attack,0255</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Entertainer's Leopard Escapes And Kills 2-Year-Old Daughter</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A leopard owned by a rock singer who
uses animals in his nightclub act escaped from its cage Wednesday
and killed the entertainer's 2-year-old daughter, officials said.
   Five leopards escaped from Joe Savage's home on 200 acres near
Ashland City, but all were captured by Wednesday night, said police
Lt. Jim Blackmore.
   Nikka Savage, mauled in her family's front yard, died at
Vanderbilt Medical Center as a result of blood loss and massive
injuries to her head and neck, said hospital spokeswoman Nancy
Humphrey.
   The leopard involved in the attack was tranquilized by wildlife
officials, and died while being transported away, Metro Nashville
police said.
   Savage, who performs heavy metal rock music in leather and wild
make-up, uses the leopards in his nightclub act. Savage was in Las
Vegas, Nev., but police said he was on his way back to Nashville
after being informed of the attack.
   A police helicopter, a professional wildcat handler and about 40
police officers joined in the search before the last escaped
animal, a 40-pound black leopard, was captured Wednesday night.
   Earlier, Police Chief Joe Casey urged parents to keep their
children indoors, saying, ``They tell us it's not dangerous but
they said that about the animal that killed the little girl.''
   Savage was treated at a Nashville hospital in 1984 after a boa
constrictor choked him during an act in which he wrapped snakes
around his neck.
</TEXT>
