<2ND_LINE>PM-Convicts Escape,170</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Convicted Murderer, Drug Dealer Escape From Youth Center</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LAUREL, Md. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two teen-agers _ one convicted of murder and
the other of dealing cocaine _ escaped from a youth detention
center outside the nation's capital, but the drug dealer was
recaptured a short time later, officials said.
   District of Columbia Human Services spokeswoman Rae Parr-Moore
said the two 17 year olds may have had outside help in their escape
Wednesday, since the fence at the Oak Hill youth center just
outside the District had been cut open from the outside.
   Oak Hill houses 155 juvenile felons from the District of
Columbia.
   Parr-Moore said the teens had been on their way to a training
exercise when they escaped through a two-foot hole in the fence.
They were discovered missing at about 9 a.m. EDT, Parr-Moore said.
   U.S. Park Police said Rashawan Gatlin was arrested later
Wednesday, but the other escapee, Fernando Smith, remained at large.
   Park Police Sergeant Karl Ore said the teens had been spotted in
an allegedly stolen car at early afternoon on the
Baltimore-Washington parkway, but that one ``bailed out of the
car'' to avoid being recaptured.
