<1ST_LINE>r a PM-WeatherpageWeather     05-26 0407</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Weatherpage Weather,0421</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Thunderstorms In Plains, Southeast</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Showers and thunderstorms dampened the southern and central High
Plains and the southern Atlantic Seaboard today after storms dumped
heavy rain on sections of South Dakota.
   Scattered showers and thunderstorms fell on the northern
Rockies, the northern High Plains, New England and the Florida
Keys. Fair skies prevailed over much of the nation's eastern half
and the Southwest.
   Frost and freeze advisories were posted for extreme western
Maryland, western Pennsylvania, West Virginia, western New York
state, lower Michigan and the eastern third of upper Michigan.
   Slow-moving thunderstorms Wednesday night dropped more than 4
inches of rain in three hours in Buffalo County, S.D., and hail the
size of golf balls, and generated 55 mph winds.
   Another thunderstorm produced hail an inch in diameter 10 miles
south of Midland in southwest Texas.
   Today's forecast called for rain in the northern Pacific Coast,
showers scattered across southeast New England, and rain showers
and thunderstorms over the southern two-thirds of Florida. Skies
were expected to be sunny over much of the rest of the nation.
   High temperatures were predicted to be in the 50s and 60s from
New England and New York to North Carolina; 60s and 70s along the
Pacific Coast and across the Pacific Northwest; 70s from the upper
Great Lakes to the Tennessee Valley, and from Alabama to Georgia,
South Carolina and northern Florida; and the 90s to near 110
degrees over the desert Southwest. Highs were expected to reach the
80s elsewhere.
   Temperatures around the nation at 3 a.m. EDT ranged from 35
degrees at Bradford, Pa., to 85 at Phoenix, Ariz.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 61 fair; Boston 50 cloudy; Buffalo 44 fair;
Charleston, S.C., 60 partly cloudy; Cincinnati 43 fair; Cleveland
41 fair; Detroit 47 fair; Miami 76 partly cloudy; New York 51
partly cloudy; Philadelphia 48 fair; Pittsburgh 39 fair; Portland,
Maine, 48 cloudy; Washington 48 fair.
   _Central: Bismarck 55 fair; Chicago 47 fair; Dallas-Fort Worth
66 cloudy; Denver 54 cloudy; Des Moines 53 fair; Indianapolis 47
fair; Kansas City 54 fair; Minneapolis-St. Paul 66 fair; Nashville
51 fair; New Orleans 72 windy; St. Louis 52 fair.
   _West: Albuquerque 61 fair; Anchorage 50 fair; Las Vegas 81
fair; Los Angeles 58 fair; Phoenix 85 fair; Salt Lake City 72
partly cloudy; San Diego 62 cloudy; San Francisco 53 fair; Seattle
54 partly cloudy.
   _Canada: Montreal 50 partly cloudy; Toronto 39 fair.
</TEXT>
