<FILEID>AP-NR-05-26-88 1033EDT</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>r a PM-BRF--Circus-Japan     05-26 0120</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Circus-Japan,0124</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Circus to Go to Japan For First Time</HEAD>
<DATELINE>VENICE, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Greatest Show on Earth will make a
16-week tour of Japan this summer in the first-ever Far East
appearance in the 118-year history of the Ringling Bros. and Barnum
& Bailey Circus.
   The tour also will mark the first time in 30 years the circus
has played under a tent.
   Kenneth Feld, owner, president and producer of the circus whose
winter headquarters are here, said there is a practical reason why
the 175 artists will perform under a tent during the tour, Feld
said.
   ``You could never fit an elephant in the doors'' of most
Japanese arenas, built mainly for sumo wrestling, he said.
</TEXT>
