<1ST_LINE>r a PM-FantasyFind     05-26 0210</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Fantasy Find,0214</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Boy Finds $4,000 and Lives It Up At Disneyland</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ANAHEIM, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 13-year-old who found a wallet stuffed
with $4,000 on a bus bench treated himself to a six-day adventure
at Disneyland, police said.
   The boy told police he had ``a ball,'' Costa Mesa Detective Paul
Cappuccilli said Wednesday.
   The boy, who was identified only as a resident of nearby Garden
Grove because of his age, found the money May 13 and rented a
$35-a-night motel room in his own name near Disneyland for nine
days from May 13-21, Cappuccilli said.
   He spent the next three days at Disneyland, buying two
skateboards, a watch, a camera and film, a gym bag and new clothes.
On his fourth day at the amusement park, the boy lost the $2,800 he
had left, the detective said.
   The next day, a 30-year-old man befriended the boy at the park
and took him to a car dealership where an employee called police.
The boy's parents, who had filed a missing persons report, were
reunited with their son May 18, Cappuccilli said.
   ``The boy knew he probably should have returned the money but
said he was having some problems at home and was planning to run
away,'' the detective said.
</TEXT>
