<1ST_LINE>u i PM-Gulf-Attack     05-26 0185</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Gulf-Attack,0191</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Iranians Attack Third Vessel Since US Broadening of Protection</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MANAMA, Bahrain (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Iranian gunboats today attacked a
Norwegian-operated oil tanker in the Strait of Hormuz and set it
ablaze.
   Persian Gulf-based shipping executives identified the stricken
tanker as the 15,530-ton liquefied petroleum gas carrier Mundogas
Rio and said it was fully laden and sailing out of the Hormuz when
attacked.
   It was the third attack by the Iranians on neutral shipping
since Washington broadened the duties of the U.S. Navy in the gulf,
allowing warships to intervene in attacks on commercial vessels,
even if they were sailing under flags other than the Stars and
Stripes.
   The executives, who spoke on condition of anonymity, said they
were not aware of any U.S. warships in the area at the time of the
attack.
   They said the captain of the vessel which flies the Liberian
flag reported a small fire aboard the vessel, but no casualties
among the crew.
   Two salvage tugboats in the vicinity rushed out to the help the
tanker, they said.
   The attacks are an offshoot of the 7{-year-old Iran-Iraq war.
</TEXT>
