<1ST_LINE>r a AM-People-Cosby     05-26 0195</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-People-Cosby,0200</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Cosby: Father's Day `Worst Day' of Man's Life</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Bill Cosby thinks Father's Day is ``the worst
day of any man's life'' and says the reason fathers don't fare as
well as mothers on their special day is because ``mothers cry and
fathers don't.''
   The comedian and other stars, including Paul Newman, John Ritter
and Tyne Daly, were interviewed about memories of their fathers in
the June issue of Woman's Day. Father's Day is June 19 this year.
   Cosby recalled how he used to shine shoes for a week before
Mother's Day to buy his mom, Anna, a present. But ``When Father's
Day came around, I'd run to the store and buy him (William Cosby
Sr.) two cigarettes _ and smoke one on the way home.''
   ``I think the reason for this difference is that mothers cry and
fathers don't,'' he said, adding:
   ``Next year I may put up billboards showing a father with a tear
running down his cheek. Maybe I'll go on a nationwide campaign with
my picture on billboards and a tear running down my cheek.
   ``I'm all for better presents on Father's Day,'' Cosby said.
</TEXT>
