<1ST_LINE>r i AM-Philippines-Crash     05-26 0174</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Philippines-Crash,0179</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Three Die In Crash of Military Plane in The Philippines</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MANILA, Philippines (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A military training plane on a test
flight crashed in the northern Philippines on Thursday and killed
three soldiers, a Philippine air force spokesman said.
   Lt. Epifanio Panzo told The Associated Press an investigation
was under way into the cause of the accident in the mountain resort
city of Baguio, 130 miles north of Manila.
   Panzo said the three-seat Marchetti FF-260 plane crashed short
of the Baguio airport and burst into flames. He said the three air
force soldiers on board died instantly.
   A radio station in Baguio monitored in Manila quoted residents
near the area as saying the plane slammed into a wall and landed on
a parked car a few miles from the airport.
   Panzo identified the victims as Maj. Amador Feleo, Lt. Roberto
Guerra and Sgt. Rafael de Castro, all of the air force's 100th
training wing unit.
   In June, 50 people were killed when a Philippine Airlines HS-748
crashed near the Baguio airport.
