<1ST_LINE>r w AM-TreasuryAuction     05-26 0099</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Treasury Auction,90</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Yields On Five-Year Treasury Notes Hit Highest Level Since 1985</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Yields on five-year Treasury notes rose in
Thursday's auction to the highest level since November 1985.
   The average yield was 8.77 percent, up from 7.65 percent at the
last auction on Feb. 25.
   It was the highest rate since five-year notes averaged 9.13
percent on Nov. 27, 1985. The notes will carry a coupon interest
rate of8.75 percent with each $10,000 in face value selling for
$9,984.30.
   A total of $7 billion in notes were sold out of bids totalling
$24.5 billion.
