<2ND_LINE>BC-Britain-Stocks, 1st Ld-Writethru,0176</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>London Shares End Little Changed</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: updates with close.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Prices on the London stock exchange settled
narrowly mixed Thursday as the market drifted amid little trading
interest.
   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-stock index was down 2.6
points, or 0.1 percent, at 1,785.3 at the close.
   Volume was 435.8 million shares, compared with Wednesday's 528.8
million shares.
   Trading was subdued before a long holiday weekend in Britain and
before Friday's release of Britain's trade data for April, dealers
said.
   Monday is a bank holiday.
   ``There have been no real inspirations as such to trade,'' one
equity salesman said. ``We've seen scraps of trades but with a
minimum amount of volume.''
   Of the 100 major stocks in the FT-SE index, 52 showed losses, 28
posted gains and 20 were unchanged.
   Dealers said the continued absence of institutional business
kept trading to a minimum.
   ``Without the confidence of institutions, why should other
investors get involved in this market?'' one equity analyst asked.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
