<1ST_LINE>u f AM-AutoProdn     05-26 0145</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Auto Prodn,0152</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Production Goes Down This Week</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Domestic automakers were scheduled to produce
245,479 cars and light trucks this week, down from last week's
262,781, Ward's Automotive Reports said Thursday.
   This week's production is higher than the same week a year ago,
when 196,890 cars and light trucks were produced, the trade journal
said.
   U.S. automakers were scheduled to make 161,768 cars this week,
compared with 171,705 a week ago and 132,594 in the same week in
1987.
   Light truck production for the week was scheduled at 83,711,
compared with last week's 91,076 and last year's 64,296.
   Canadian automakers were to build 22,134 cars this week, down
from 24,511 a week ago and up from last year's 17,193.
   Canadian light truck production was scheduled at 17,197,
compared with 16,321 a week ago and 18,244 in the same week last
year.
</TEXT>
