<TEXT>
   Stock prices pieced together a small gain
Thursday as the market absorbed the news of stronger economic
growth in the first quarter of the year.
   The Dow Jones average of 30 industrials rose 5.38 to 1,966.75.
   Advancing issues outnumbered declines by about 4 to 3 in
nationwide trading of New York Stock Exchange-listed stocks, with
787 up, 592 down and 543 unchanged.
