<HEAD>London Home on Market; Claimed World's Priciest</HEAD>
<NOTE>EDS: SUBS lede to CORRECT age of house to 170 years sted 179;
picks up 2nd graf pvs bg'ng, The 26,000-square-foot ...</NOTE>
<DATELINE>BEVERLY HILLS, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Holme, a 170-year-old London
mansion claimed to be the world's most expensive dwelling, is on
the market for about $58 million, a California real estate agent
said Thursday.
   The 26,000-square-foot house in prestigious Regents Park sits on
4.5 acres of landscaped, terraced grounds. It features a grand
dining room, a library, and an all-weather tennis court, said Mike
Silverman, an agent who specializes in accommodations for the rich
and famous.
   The Holme was designed by Decimus Burton and completed in 1818.
Modern amenities include eight garages, luxury elevators, sauna,
whirlpool bath and exercise rooms.
   Silverman, who said he has an exclusive listing for the Holme,
claimed the asking price, 30 million pounds sterling, is the
highest sought anywhere.
   The identities of the occupants were not revealed.
   ``There's a family that lives there whose lifestyle has
changed,'' said Jane Harman, a spokeswoman for Silverman. She added
that the house has been on the market for several weeks.
