<1ST_LINE>u f AM-Japan-Markets 1stLd-Writethru f0287 05-26 0146</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Japan-Markets, 1st Ld-Writethru, f0287,0148</2ND_LINE>
<NOTE>EDS: RECASTS throughout to UPDATE with morning trading; No pickup</NOTE>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The U.S. dollar gained moderately against the
Japanese yen in morning trading Thursday, while Tokyo share prices
also rose.
   After opening at 124.35 yen, up only 0.05 yen from Wednesday's
close, the dollar continued to edge up and was changing hands at
about 124.43 yen at late morning.
   On the Tokyo Stock Exchange, the Nikkei stock average of 225
selected issues, which gained 130.99 points Wednesday, added
another 48.26 points, or 0.17 percent, to close the morning session
at 27,491.91. The Tokyo market's leading barometer hit a
mid-morning high of 27,641.49 points, but then fell on
profit-taking in heavy trading.
   Traders said Wednesday's dip on Wall Street did not discourage
investors in Tokyo stocks. The dollar's strength reflected a strong
closing Wednesday in New York, they said.
</TEXT>
